<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida1de1112-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95" identifier="/us/usc/t32/s902"><num value="902">§ 902.</num><heading> Homeland defense activities: funds</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Defense may provide funds to a Governor to employ National Guard units or members to conduct homeland defense activities that the Secretary determines to be necessary and appropriate for participation by the National Guard units or members, as the case may be.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida1de1113-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/108/375/dA/tV/s512/a/1">Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title V, § 512(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="2004-10-28">Oct. 28, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/1878">118 Stat. 1878</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/109/364/dA/tX/s1071/b/1">Pub. L. 109–364, div. A, title X, § 1071(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-17">Oct. 17, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/2400">120 Stat. 2400</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/115/232/dA/tX/s1081/b">Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title X, § 1081(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-08-13">Aug. 13, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/1985">132 Stat. 1985</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
